post_text: Humphrey Public School is accepting applications for a 5-Day Special Education Paraprofessional for the 2020-2021 school year. Applicants must pass the Project Para course to become ‚ÄúHighly Qualified‚Äù and a successful background check. Applicants must also be able to communicate effectively and work with students of special needs, as well as carry out teacher directives. Interested applicants should complete an application for Classified Employees located on our school web page at http://www.humphreybulldogs.org/. Please send to Greg Sjuts, Superintendent, Humphrey Public School, 405 South 7thStreet, Humphrey NE 68642-0278. Applications will be taken until positions are filled. EOE

post_text:
Congratulations to Allie S. on her selection as a participant for the Northeast Community College and Central Community College 2020 All-Star teams. Unfortunately, these contests will not be played this year. During her senior season, Allie was HLHF's team and floor captain. She earned First-Team All-Conference honors, Norfolk Daily News First Team All Area, Lincoln Journal Star and Prep Dig All-State Third Team, Omaha World Herald All-State Honorable Mention, and was named to the Under Armour All-American Watch List. She holds the following HLHF records: 4th in aces in one game, 4th digs in a game, 4th in assists for a season, 3rd in career kills, 3rd in career ace blocks, 2nd in digs in a season, 2nd in career digs, 2nd in career aces, 2nd in assists in a game, 2nd in assists for a season, and 1st in career assists. Allie will continue her career at Mid Plains Community College in North Platte. Congratulations on an incredible career as a Bulldog, Allie, and best of luck as a Knight!
#GoBulldogs #HPSBulldogs #BeKind #GreatDayToBeABulldogüêæ #AllStar #GoKnights
